<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-10-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="183" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d183">
                    <head>No. 182.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hunter</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Angell</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-10-06"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 6,
                            1881</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 126.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 190, of July 28 last,
                        relative to the purchase of land by foreigners at Canton, has been received,
                        and your action, with respect to that subject, is approved.</p>
                    <p>I am, sir, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>W. HUNTER,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting
                        Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>